Package org.cyclops.cyclopscore.nbt.path.parse

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    INbtPathExpressionParseHandler
    Handles a string representation of an NBT path expression.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    INbtPathExpressionParseHandler.HandleResult
    A result data object for INbtPathExpressionParseHandler.
    NbtPathExpressionExecutionContext
    A context that is passed during the NBT path execution.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerAllChildren
    A handler that handles follows all child links of a tag via "*".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerAllChildren.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalAdapter
    An abstract handler that handles boolean relational expressions.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalAdapter.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalEqual
    A handler that handles boolean expressions in the form of " == 10".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalGreaterThan
    A handler that handles boolean expressions in the form of " > 10".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalGreaterThanOrEqual
    A handler that handles boolean expressions in the form of " ≥ 10".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalLessThan
    A handler that handles boolean expressions in the form of " < 10".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerBooleanRelationalLessThanOrEqual
    A handler that handles boolean expressions in the form of " ≤ 10".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerChild
    A handler that handles child path expressions in the form of ".childName", where the matched string represents the child name that should be navigated in.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerChild.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerChildBrackets
    A handler that handles child path expressions in the form of "["childName"]", where the matched string represents the child name that should be navigated in.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerCurrent
    A handler that picks the current position in the NBT tree via "@".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerCurrent.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerFilterExpression
    A handler that handles filter expressions in the form of "[?(expression)]", such as "[?(@.childName)]" or "[?(@.childName < 10)]".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerFilterExpression.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerLength
    A handler that handles child path expressions for ".length", to retrieve the length of lists and tag compounds.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerLength.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerListElement
    A handler that handles list element expressions in the form of "[10]", where the matched string represents the list element index that should be navigated in.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerListElement.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerListSlice
    A handler that handles list slice expressions in the form of "[start:end:step]" such as "[2:3:2]".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerListSlice.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerParent
    A handler that picks the parent of the NBT tree in the current execution context via "..".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerParent.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerRoot
    A handler that picks the root of the NBT tree via "$".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerRoot.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerStringEqual
    A handler that handles boolean expressions in the form of " == "abc"".
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerStringEqual.Expression  
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerUnion
    A handler that handles union expressions in the form of "[10,12]" or "[10,]" or "[,12]", where the matches indicate the children or list elements that should be matched.
    NbtPathExpressionParseHandlerUnion.Expression
